# Testing Standards

## Directory Structure

All tests live in `__tests__/` at the project root, mirroring source structure:

```
__tests__/
├── fixtures/           # ALL test data lives here
│   ├── *.fixture.ts    # Static test literals (MOCK_ prefix)
│   ├── factories/      # Dynamic builders (build prefix)
│   └── index.ts        # Barrel export
├── unit/
│   ├── core/domain/    # Entity tests
│   └── core/use-cases/ # Use case tests
├── integration/
│   ├── api/            # API route tests
│   └── features/       # Feature integration tests
└── e2e/                # End-to-end tests
```

## Test Data: Always Use Fixtures

**All mock data MUST be defined in `__tests__/fixtures/` and imported.** Never hardcode test data inline.

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
import { MOCK_CREATE_TASK_DTO } from "@/__tests__/fixtures"
it("should create a task", async () => {
  const result = await createTask(MOCK_CREATE_TASK_DTO)
  expect(result.title).toBe(MOCK_CREATE_TASK_DTO.title)
})

// ❌ WRONG — hardcoded test data
it("should create a task", async () => {
  const result = await createTask({ title: "Some task", priority: "high" })
})
```

## Fixture Conventions

- **Static fixtures** (`*.fixture.ts`): `MOCK_` prefix for stable known data
- **Factory functions** (`factories/*.factory.ts`): `build` prefix with override support
- **Barrel export**: All fixtures export from `__tests__/fixtures/index.ts`

## Test Naming Convention

```
[entity].[layer].test.ts

Examples: task.entity.test.ts, create-task.use-case.test.ts, tasks-api.integration.test.ts
```

## What to Test by Layer

| Layer | Focus | Tool |
|-------|-------|------|
| Domain Entities | Business rules, state transitions | Jest |
| Use Cases | Orchestration with mocked ports | Jest |
| API Routes | Request/response, status codes | Jest + Supertest |
| Components | Rendering, user interactions | React Testing Library |
| E2E | Critical user journeys | Playwright/Cypress |
